canonical:
  title: 文奎讓千牛衛大將軍不允
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 永惟睿考臨御三韓十有八年振威四方制敵千里非夫番番良士仡仡勇夫竭力盡忠折衝禦侮亦何以致此哉朕奉承先業大賚庶工以示從事邊陲服勞營衛肆陞大將之位俾帥三軍之師宜體至懷往膺休命
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 文奎讓千牛衛大將軍不允
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 永惟睿考。臨御三韓。十有八年。振威四方。制敵千里。非夫番番良士仡仡勇夫。竭力盡忠折衝禦侮。亦何以致此哉。朕奉承先業。大賚庶工。以示從事邊陲。服勞營衛。肆陞大將之位。俾帥三軍之師。宜體至懷。往膺休命。
korean:
  title: 문규 양 천우위 대장군 불윤
  author: 무명씨
  language: kor
  text: 선고(先考)이신 예종(睿宗)께서 삼한(三韓)에 군림하신 지 18년 동안에 사방에 위엄을 떨치고 천리 밖에서 적을 제압하셨는데, 어진 선비와 용맹한 장사들이 힘을 다하고 충성을 기울여 싸우고 막지 않았다면 어찌 이를 이루었겠는가.짐이 선왕의 업을 새로 이어 어진 신하들에게 크게 상을 내려 변경에서 복무하고 호위에 애쓴 공로를 표창하고자 한다. 이에 그대를 대장의 직위에 올려 삼군을 거느리는 장수로 삼노니, 마땅히 지극한 나의 뜻을 알아서 나아가 영광스러운 명을 받을지어다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0330_010_0220&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Decree Appointing Mun Kyui to the Position of General of the Thousand Bull Guard, Which He Respectfully Declined
  author: Anonymous
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I have long contemplated how my illustrious father held dominion over the Three Han for eighteen years, extending his might across the four quarters and subduing enemies at a thousand li distance. Yet this could never have been achieved without the virtue of worthy scholars and the valor of stalwart warriors, who exhausted their strength and poured forth their loyalty in defense and resistance.

    I, inheriting the legacy of my predecessor, now bestow great rewards upon worthy officials to honor their labors on the frontiers and their devoted service in the royal guard. Therefore, I raise you to the rank of Great General, commanding the three armies. You must understand the profundity of my intentions and advance to receive this glorious mandate.
  footnotes:
    - Yeongje (睿宗) refers to King Seongjong's father, whose reign lasted approximately eighteen years
    - The 'Three Han' (三韓) is a classical reference to Korea, reflecting the ancient kingdoms of Goguryeo, Baekje, and Silla
    - The 'three armies' refers to the traditional three divisions of the military forces
    - This appears to be a royal edict of appointment that Mun Kyui respectfully declined, suggesting a record of his refusal to accept high office
